---
description: Next.js App Router patterns
globs:
  - "src/app/**/*.ts"
  - "src/app/**/*.tsx"
  - "src/actions/**/*.ts"
  - "src/actions/**/*.tsx"
---

Next.js architecture rules:
- Default to server components
- Add "use client" only when necessary
- Server components may fetch data directly with Prisma or other server-side I/O
- Prefer Server Actions for create/update/delete flows
- After mutations, use the appropriate revalidation/navigation pattern instead of inventing ad hoc cache logic
- Keep page.tsx and layout.tsx focused on composition
- Move non-trivial logic into feature helpers, queries, or server utilities

Data fetching rules:
- Prefer server-side data fetching for initial page loads
- Avoid client-side fetching for data that can be rendered on the server
- Avoid introducing TanStack Query unless the use case clearly needs client-side server-state management
- If proposing TanStack Query, explicitly justify why server rendering + Server Actions are not enough

Route handler rules:
- Do not create route handlers just to proxy internal database access
- Use route handlers for webhooks, third-party callbacks, public APIs, or cases that truly require an HTTP boundary

Form rules:
- Prefer server-first form handling with Server Actions
- Keep validation authoritative on the server even if client validation also exists